169
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:38,050
The police changed in five years.

170
00:07:38,050 --> 00:07:41,620
In 2014, the police officers were mostly polite.

171
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:43,349
There were a few clashes,

172
00:07:43,349 --> 00:07:46,199
and there were a few police groups that were
more troublesome.

173
00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:50,270
But the main body of police just tried to
protect everyone.

174
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:52,349
When I was in Hong Kong last month,

175
00:07:52,349 --> 00:07:54,419
it was completely different.

176
00:07:54,419 --> 00:07:57,669
The police are out of control, and violent.

177
00:07:57,669 --> 00:08:00,030
Yes, there are rumors that some of them

178
00:08:00,030 --> 00:08:02,379
have been brought in from mainland China.

179
00:08:02,379 --> 00:08:04,970
That might explain why they’re acting like
mainland thugs.

180
00:08:04,970 --> 00:08:07,330
But so far, those are just rumors.

181
00:08:07,330 --> 00:08:09,400
But either way, Hong Kong police commanders

182
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:12,330
have pretty much given the officers carte
blanche

183
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:14,360
to do whatever they want.

184
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:17,819
Plus, they’re wearing masks but no ID badges,

185
00:08:17,819 --> 00:08:21,659
and there’s a law against doxxing them.

186
00:08:21,659 --> 00:08:24,610
So they have the protection of being anonymous.

187
00:08:24,610 --> 00:08:27,520
On top of that, they’re overworked and stressed

188
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:32,320
from five months of continuous protests.

189
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:35,680
This is a recipe for disaster.

190
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:39,380
It doesn’t even require loyalty to the CCP.

